{
  "texts": [
    "On this held-out test set, the final model had an AUROC of 0.81 and AP of 0.77.",
    "Feature space analysisFeatures for the weakly supervised tile-based model were generated and visualized for both datasets using the included feature generation interface.",
    "Features are generated through calculation of post-convolutional layer activations for all image tiles, and the resulting feature space is visualized through UMAP dimensionality reduction.",
    "UMAP plots of the TCGA and University of Chicago feature spaces show good class separation between HPV-negative and HPV-positive images for both the training and test data (Fig. 12, A and B).",
    "The mosaic map for the University of Chicago feature space highlights known biologically-relevant image features associated with HPV status (Fig. 12E)."
  ]
}